dataIdInfo.idAbs: THIS ARCGIS FEATURE CLASS WAS ORIGINALLY CREATED IN 1996. CURRENTLY IT IS CREATED NEW EVERY NIGHT FROM THE ADDCLC FEATURE CLASS WHICH IS MAINTAINED DAILY BY THE CITY ENGINEER'S OFFICE AND THE COUNTY PLANNING OFFICE. THE ADDCLC ONLY CONTAINS THE ADDRID, BUILDING NUMBER, STREET NAME, NUMBER OF UNITS, SPACE NUMBER, ZIP CODE, AND ASSIGNED DATE. THE ADDCLC IS SPATIALLY JOINED TO 16 OTHER FEATURE CLASSES TO CREATE THIS NEW FEATURE CLASS. THE OTHER FEATURE CLASSES ADDED TO THIS POINT FEATURE CLASS INCLUDE LEGAL DESCRIPTIONS, ZONING, VOTING DISTRICTS, SPECIAL FLOOD HAZARD AREAS, FIRE RESPONSE, OWNERSHIP, TOWN NAME, TOWNSHIP-RANGE-SECTION, ETC.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The purpose of this dataset is to identify the approximate location of structures in Cheyenne and Laramie County with assigned site addresses.
